<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[67059]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA["Els contes de l'Estrella" at the Tantarantana]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<b>Theatre.</b> A musical story full of light and poetry for children over the age of 3, performed using Chinese shadow theatre techniques.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p><em>High up there the stars shine in the black of night,</em><br />
<em>and down here, the sea rests like a marine-blue mirror.</em><br />
<em>Sitting on the moon&#8217;s lap,</em><br />
<em>the little star sings songs and tells stories.</em></p>
<p>This is the start of <em>El Conte de l&#8217;Estrelleta </em>[The Tale of the Little Star], at the Teatre Tantarantana. The star comes down to Earth to tell us stories for all the family. The show uses Chinese shadow theatre techniques, using hands to cast shadows with a variety of original shapes on a wall or screen .</p>
